caption: Incredible food/drinks and absolutely amazing service! Everyone that works here is happy to teach  and recommend games. Can't recommend this place highly enough!
Great place to have lunch and play a few games with friends.
The General Manager Zack is a super cool guy and made the dining experience awesome.  Will totally go back for more knowledge on all things awesome.

This was my 1st time here and what won me over is Zac the general manager and our waitress Sarica. Their customer service was the best I've had in a very long time. They were both very attentive. Zac took the time to explain how to play a few of the games to us which we love. I live a hr away but will come again in a heart beat.
Yum, latte, and games!
Insane board game selection and well made coffee drinks

Before COVID, I would come here to do a lot of work (not doing that now because not doing indoor dining). The coffee drinks are pretty good. The staff are nice. Major bonus to them for providing some first aid to me after I tripped on the sidewalk outside and came in bleeding profusely.  I've stuck with takeout coffee from here since COVID and that hasn't disappointed.
Such a cool idea. Will be coming back!
Great food, coffee, drinks, games, and people.
Awesome local eats.
Nice spot to grab a coffee or tea then walk around campus.
Loved this place.
They are open, and delivering.
I love love love Board & Brew! Great for dates, family outings, or treating yourself. Do yourself a favor and try Ben's Abomination and a Londoner
Super fast, very friendly service. Food is mediocre.

Great board game café!  Food menu sticks to the basics (burgers, sandwiches, salads, soups) but does them decently.  You can also order beer, wine, and cocktails.  Definitely a staple of College Park!

Love this place! Great coffee, food and service! Best place for breakfast in College Park! Update: The owners of Board and Brew are wonderful people. We reached out to them at the start of the pandemic about purchasing games from them. They were very responsive and we arranged a pickup. At the pickup they also lent us another game for free that our kids could play. It was an amazing and thoughtful gesture that my family has not forgotten.

We also ordered some main courses for lunch and everything was on point. The lunch prices are very reasonable and the staff is very attentive. Stunning and magnificent, a true delight to experience. Not to miss.
Perfect spot to go if you want to have fun, kill time,  or have a different kind of date night. The food and drinks are good, the staff is helpful, and the games are plentiful!

You get ALOT of food for the price. Breakfast food is pretty good.  Butter Croissant were very good. Pancakes are fluffy and good.  Eggs are great and cooked to order (had over easy and scrambled).  Home fries were unevenly diced (some as small as diced shoestring fries, others were cubed potatoes and everything in between) but tasted ok.  Everything Bagel sandwiches are huge.  The coconut-orange bread is a little dry, but has a great marmalade flavor, so just add some butter on it and you'll enjoy.
Amazing place, great service, extremely friendly and fun staff and delicious food. Pesto chicken sandwich is a must try. A variety of board games to play. The staff really knows their menu well.
This was a cool visit with a vibrant atmosphere and delicious food. Zac was great!

I've come here for a birthday party (they were able to accommodate our desire for it to be outdoors with spaced-out seating), studying, a coffee date, and hanging out with friends. At every occasion the service has been praiseworthy and the food wholly enjoyable (if you're a fan of latte art, The Board and Brew is for you).

I have stopped in to work a couple times the past 2 months since I moved here and I will keep coming back! I love to try new places but since I came here the first time the service, chai latte and food are incredible —why do I need to go anywhere else? There is inside and outside seating and I feel safe during COVID. This coffee house reminds me a lot of the one I would frequent back home and I just feel like the people who work here are kind and legit care about the community and their business and those who frequent it! Please try the chai latte, I’m serious! It’s the best I’ve ever had and I love that you all are open late too! Makes me happy to know I have a tried and true selected already for coffee 😘

This is the perfect place for any occasion and I know for a fact that I’ll be coming back again. From the drinks, to the appetizers, to the entrees - there’s not much that I can said besides fantastic!
The absolute best  food in town! Never a bad meal here. Amazing service in a wonderful setting. Highly recommended!

Ordered food, estimated time was 15-20 minutes took 45. The manager was rude to the customer before me and was constantly stopping to train employees further backing up the tickets...my food is cold now. To top it all off, i found a small black hair in my breakfast, disgusting  Ownership reached out to me immediately and issued a refund. Thank you for redeeming your service record, I couldn’t have asked for a better experience.

Superb service! Their game recommendations are always spot on. Food is good and the drinks are better. My only wish is that the cocktails were a bit bigger. It's quality not quantity, I get it. Either way, I highly recommend this place.

Zack was very hospitable and eager and informed with his service. He was also attentive and upbeat as well. At first I thought it was a bit much but quickly appreciated his knowledge and willingness to make sure that I was taken care of. This is a nice break from the surrounding areas and the atmosphere was more west coast chill which I really appreciated. I am only giving three stars because they only had one red wine as an option and no open bar, I was really hoping to get an espresso martini. This place has potential to be more than what it is and the concept of brews and board games is very appealing. I would have stayed longer to do some schoolwork but the chairs were not very comfortable and I would imagine it’s because of COVID.. ah what the heck I will gift it four stars because is worth giving it a shot.. why not? Xo thanks Zack and Kenny 👌🏽
We had a fantastic  in this restaurant. We loved the extraordinary vibes and the menu. The staff are very amiable. I am glad we ultimately decided to visit this spot.
Amazing service, enthusiastic and extremely helpful. Zak was the best host I have ever encountered. I recommend this spot to everyone.
Totally my place!!! The food is very extraordinary and absolutely outstanding.

We ordered two bagel sandwiches (amazing), hash browns (seasoned perfectly), and two coffees through their online portal. Only the food arrived so I called and the employees were so kind and said they would personally drive the drinks (and complimentary pastries!) over to us. They were here in 10 minutes. Honest mistake rectified immediately by the awesome staff here! Oh and the coffees were well worth the wait, I highly recommend the Spiced Kyoto Cold Brew!! Will definitely be a returning customer. Thanks!

Great restaurant. Plenty of paid parking in the garage behind the restaurant. Their coffee is excellent. I believe they primarily use Counter Culture beans. Friendly staff and a great outdoor patio with table service.

Amazing little hidden gem! It was my date and I’s first time meeting in person so we picked a place neither of us had been. I loved the ambiance as soon as we walked in and Zack greeted us immediately! As someone who also works in the industry (casino bartender) I cannot say enough good things about Zack! He’s extremely knowledgeable about everything on the menu, the hundreds of games available for playing, and the local area as well! He made great menu recommendations (the pretzel bites were so yummy) and my cocktail was made to perfection! It was a little slow on a Wednesday night but we stayed and talked until closing and did not feel rushed at all. An old boss at the first place I bartended said “whether there’s 1 person at your bar or 100, entertain them the same” and Zack did that. We will definitely be returning 😊
Great place to hangout with friends they got all kinds of games. And their food is really yummy too specially their sweet potato fries!
Even in times of Covid, they still deliver great food and quality board games
An amazing dining experience. The food, atmosphere, and overall sense of whimsy is truly something special.
The menu and service were above our expectations. We surely loved the environment of this place. Excellent spot to take my family out for lunch.
Great concept. Great food. Solid service. Relatively affordable.
Great atmosphere and super friendly, engaged staff. Go support them once the quarantine ends!
Bagels are amazing. Staff is super cool
Never had the food. I didn't know this place existed.

Great atmosphere, wide selection of board games, wide selection of food including beer and coffee, and the food tastes good.  I really want to give this place five stars, but the service is a serious problem because you can go several hours without even seeing a waiter and the staff at the counter will tell you to wait for your water if you try to order from them directly.  My family member came here during the day when they weren't busy and they took over an hour to deliver TEA (hot water + bag). She never actually got the tea, because she only had the hour to wait. She would was supposed to order food when the waiter came back, but that also never happened.

Food was very good, board game selection was definitely adequate to meet to very broad range of board game players. Very popular place good atmosphere. Spiked milkshakes far too sweet with a lot going on, Just needs to be a classic milkshake with a good bit of bourbon if you ask me...
Great food,games, and overall service!

Have 2, 4, 8 hours to kill? The Board and Brew is an easy hang out board room cafe with a nice cosy atmosphere and casual American food  Love this place for it's extensive board game collection and recommendations from the game master. Will visit again and again.
Great place, great vibe, great service, great staff, great food, overall friendly and welcoming. Had a great time here!
Server - a blonde chick was super energetic but didn't listen very well.  But the food and games are great.   A nice place that still has a bit of intimacy
I have been eating breakfast here for a couple months. I love the Sandwiches ,the breakfast platters and the smoothies. I highly recommend Ben's Abomination .
Board and Brew always offers the best service, food, and board games of course! Be prepared to spend some money, but it is always worth it. They have something for everyone.

All I have to say about the place is the games. I didn't get to play any but they have almost any game you could want, they appear to be in great shape, the staff know about them, and they're well organized! OMG!  I should also mention the food is delicious, the art is great, and they have tables with chairs or couches.
Definitely a fun concept. Wide variety of board games and great food, albeit pricey. Fun for a first date or going to hang out with friends.

My husband and I went here on a whim one Friday, and wow! What a cool place. It's not hard to find, as it's facing the road (but parking is pretty much exclusively paid in a garage attached to the rear of the building, just FYI).  The place has a modern, thoughtful layout. There are large windows up front for those that want daylight, and a dimmer area in the back if you're not feeling the sunshine. The many shelves are lined with games for every type of tabletop experience. There are different seating options, tables with chairs or couches and armchairs. The bathrooms have chalkboard walls to write on, which is so unique!  There are so, so many board games to try. The price for unlimited play is fair but varies based on the time of day. You don't have to pay the fee if you bring your own game though, which is cool! You can also buy board games, art on the walls, and trading card boosters. My husband and I played MtG Commander that we'd brought along, and didn't feel like we were scrutinized for the choice to play our own game.  Food and drink-wise, everything is pretty standardly priced for a specialized cafe. In the drink department, they sell select sodas, teas, coffee drinks, and alcoholic beverages. As far as food, they've got restaurant-fare entrees, smaller plates, appetizers, and snacks. We loved their Oreo milkshake and orange float, as well as their pretzel bites(those dips were killer!).  During our experience, the atmosphere was fun, friendly, and relaxed. Our server Sam was so welcoming and attentive. One of the owners stopped by our table to chat and definitely seems to love his business as much as he loves his customers.  Overall, this was a great experience. We hope to come back within a few months as we're from out of town, but boy do we wish we could go every day!
Awesome staff, huge selection of games, and good food!
Food was blah and overpriced. Got chicken pesto sandwich with side salad. Chicken was rubber and greens were wilted. Waited long for my lunch even when restaurant was nearly empty. Was not pleased.

very different atmosphere than most places with all the board games and couches. Food was good but a bit expensive, $12 for a pesto chicken sandwich. Service was extremely nice and made the experience better than normal.

Great for what is advertised in the name. A great place to try out new games or get friends together to play classics. Their alcoholic drinks and coffee are great as well. Beyond that there are issues. The food ranges from fine to gross and is often over priced for what you get. My friends and I have solved that by just eating before hand whenever we go. Their "game gurus" are another issue for me. Usually very annoying and socially inept. I dont like getting bombarded whenever I'm seen reading the rules for a game, only to have the guru spend the same amount of time reading the rules to try and explain it to me. I understand having the guru as a resource available, but right now they are intrusive and annoying. One, the guy with a mohawk and a beard, actually made fun of me for seeing me have the rulebook open for reference while we played. Did not appreciate that.  Dont let my complaints fool you, I love Board and Brew and me and my friends always visit at least once a month. Good games, good drinks, good atmosphere, just could use some work in some areas.
Cafe first with great food and beer.  Helpful manager that seems to know quite a bit about games.  Highly recommend to any and all nerds looking for a good afternoon of fun
Fun

Unique and fun experience. My husband and our boys (10-12) had a wonderful family dinner and game night. We arrived around 5:30 on a Saturday night and were able to get a table no problem. We paid $5 per person (under 10 free) to play games till 1am. They have every game you can think of and more. It's an organized and efficient system. We're took a break from playing games to eat some burgers, which were good. The Old Bay fries and pretzel bites were our favorite. The service was good and no one rushed us. Recommend giving it a try if you enjoy playing games.
Great game selection, friendly staff, decent coffee, also hot and iced teas
So many great games! I love that they have a game master to help you chose between them all.
Good prices and great games. Food is good for all diets, including vegans.
Great food and service, super friendly staff, and plenty of fun for many hours
Mike's mystery chicken sandwich is so good black bean burger is a must try.
Delicious food, fun board games! Ben's abomination (on the breakfast menu) was pretty darn good!

I tried Brew Burger for the first time and it going to be my last. When I ordered the burger everything come to cold/Tomato /Bread. I had to ask if it can be warm. After a few hours later I fell pain in my stomach with fever. I went to my doctor and she said I had a food virus. So stay away from this place.

Amazing collection of strategy games, but really limited selection of party games (which are easier to play given that the tables aren’t very big.) They didn’t have Red Flags, What Do You Meme?, or any expansion packs for Cards Against Humanity- just the original. The food selection is great and tasty, but the non-alcoholic drink selection was really limited and strange (ex. chocolate banana soda). They didn’t have coke, sprite, ginger ale, anything like that. I would be more willing to make this a regular hang out spot for my friends and I if they improved these things and/or maybe allowed people to bring their own games. Also, finding the place and getting the parking machine to work was frustrating. Only 1/4 of our cards worked with the machine.
I love coming here. The games and food is great. The staff is really nice. They have discount days during the week.
It's costly and the food doesn't taste great.. Simply it's not worth the money
Fantastic place. Here's the deal: - Pay $5 per person per day - Play unlimited board games (nothing digital) - great food - great beer / wine list - great coffee house atmosphere
Great place! Chill atmosphere with delicious food! Didn't play a game, but their collection was impressive!
More board games than I knew existed.  Good beer selection, and tasty food. Would have been 5 stars if our server had given a decent apology after dropping a board game on my wife's shoulder.

Excellent cafe with great food. They have a huge collection of board games to choose from. The food is delicious with plenty of vegan and vegetarian options. The atmosphere is relaxeed and friendly. The staff members are really helpful. The Portobello mushroom sandwich (picture) is truly mouth watering.

Absolutely incredible collection of games, very friendly staff, and very comfortable.  Food is pretty good too. Only potential issue is that some games require bigger tables than the ones they have available, so it's hard to play certain games.  Again, phenomenal selection of games.
Great selections of games and good food. Staff is always friendly and willing to help you pick/teach the games.
Great ambiance and good board games. Old Bay fries highly recommended.

Everything about this place is amazing!! The atmosphere was great, the service was superb, the eggnog flat white was perhaps the best drink i've ever had... So impressed. Will definitely come back here!!
Board and brew has become one of my favorite establishments, the food and service is amazing.
Great food, an array of games, and a nice vibes. It's a cool place to hang out.

Fun and cool spot! Would be five stars if they played a more chill and acoustic soundtrack. The dance music made me feel like I was in an arcade with a DDR machine not a coffee spot with board games. Good food and drinks! Definitely check it out.

Love the games, staff are all awesome, but food was disappointing. Not our first outing here. Hummus with veggie option used to actually be veggies- carrots, peppers, and a decent amount of hummus. I paid $7 for a tablespoon of hummus covered with pickled onion and served with 8-10 pieces of celery.  Hope it was just an off night.
I found out about this place from uber eats. Breakfast was so good I went to visit this place. Who knew such good food would come from that kitchen!

I love the vibe of this place! My sisters and I spent hours playing board games here. They have almost every game you can think of and a whole bunch more. The staff can teach you how to play any game of your choice.The food and drinks were delicious. There is a small fee to play games, but if you purchase a certain amount in food/drinks, playing games are complimentary.  The service was great. Student artwork decorate the walls.
Creamy tomato soup is awesome.
Very nice staff, good food and cold brew
Great location to get delicious coffee, food and play/buy games.  If I am in the area again someday, I'll be back.

Fun family night. Food was excellent. I had the Korean Pulled Pork sandwich and it was delicious. It was fun to try new games and the “game guru” did a great job selecting and explaining a few game options for us so that we could choose ones that were the best fit. Definitely will go back!
Food and coffee we're both good. Staff was nice, the place draws a big crowd for their board games, so there's no telling how long your wait might be, pretty worth it though!

We went Monday and Tuesday Nov. 18th and 19th. The first day it was explained to us that on Monday and Tuesday gaming was complimentary if you spent $12 on food and drinks.  Before we went on Tuesday, I double checked this on the website and it verified that on Tuesday gaming would be free if we spent $12 or more on food or drinks.  (Image of their website is attached to review).  But the waitress on Tuesday told us they changed this recently and they would not honor it.  I said, "even if it's still on your website"?  She said, "no, we don't do it anymore, we just haven't updated the site yet".  She didn't go ask the manager if they'd honor it since they're still advertising it or anything.  It didn't ruin our night.  We still played games, and had food and drinks.  But it's super misleading and dishonest to not honor an advertisement that brought us in.  Again, the waitress on Monday said it was for both days.  The waitress on Tuesday said the first waitress and the website we're wrong and charged us for games.  I'm attempting to upload an image of the website showing the Monday/Tuesday deal, but it doesn't seem to want to accept the file.  If Board and Brew would like to contact me about this experience, i'd be happy to send them the image, if it doesn't post here.

Really fun little place. Drinks and food range but are mostly quite affordable for the high quality. Server was really nice. According to him, they make a lot of things in house, and the pesto definitely tasted like it
Awesome date location!

We played using paperclips to replace several missing game pieces and had to piece together to the multiple pieces of the necessary guide books used each session. It was also strange that the games charge was listed on the same receipt and suggested that we tip based in that amount in addition to our drinks and food (no service was provided for the games).  Otherwise, it's a nice atmosphere and would be a fun place to be.
(Translated by Google) Nice to play or have breakfast  (Original) Agradable para jugar o desyunar

Board games, burgers, breakfast, coffee, and beer. What more do you need? I love this place. The DMV has a massive shortage of coffee shops that are open late, and it's fortune that this one is open late on weekends. It typically has a college crowd and can get a little loud during peak times, but the servers and staff are always awesome.
Excellent good.  Wonderful people.  Really like the atmosphere here.  Had the spicy Buffalo chicken sandwich with sweet potato fries which was excellent.

The place has a a nice decor and the food was  very good. The sweet potato fries are amazing. I heard the coffee is excellent too. But I haven’t tried. This place has a lot of board games, if you are into board games then it’s a must visit place. You have to park on the opposite side of the building though. It was loud when I went because many people were talking.

I don't even play board games here, it's a wonderful spot to relax with friends or meet new people and have dinner or a drink. I have enjoyed their menu, and it changes fairly often.  We used to get their fussy caramel popcorn and go on dates when there was live music or an open mic. Now it's our extra living room when we're catching up with friends from DC/UMD.
Tasty food and fun games!!!
Love the ambience.  Good food and the concept of games with a "game sommelier" who advices you on game recommendations based on your tastes.
Top notch board game library/place for Magic events. Also has really nice food service! Highly recommend, there's no place like it.

(Translated by Google) Really cool. Although a little noisy but it is often the case. Good timing service at the top you can have an explanation of rules for the chosen game.  (Original) Vraiment cool. Quoi qu un peu bruyant mais c est souvent le cas. Bon moment service au top tu peux avoir une explication de règles pour le jeu choisi.
service was great.  the food ranged from great to good
Love it

Other than paying for parking, this place is amazing. Great weekly offers, trendy crowds, great selection of games and food. Healthy options and diverse menu. Fantastic atmosphere and seating. Great stop to hang out near UMD campus.
Love coming here for date night, the service is always very welcoming, I was here last Thursday and had lots of fun!
One of the best Old bay fries!
My wife and I come here for late night fun. The food is OK, but the drinks and games are great.
Good coffee and breakfast all day.

I think 3 stars is rather generous based on my experience here last night.  Let's start with the good.  The food was tasty. The drink recipes were tasty. The concept of the restaurant is a great concept. Come in with friends, pay a $5 cover and choose one of their hundreds of awesome and unique board games to play, with no limit on which games or play time. And while you play you can eat lunch/dinner or drink gourmet specialized coffee/tea or some other hand made drink.  Unfortunately the execution of this idea was bad enough to make the overall experience unpleasant. I will not come back here on my own. If someone else hosts an event here, I'll reluctantly come, but I won't bring my friends here.  The coffee I ordered came out barely above lukewarm. The food orders for our table came out so haphazardly that it was awkward to try and play the games, and it was also awkward to eat, being one of only a few people that had food. I ordered way after my event's host and I ordered at the same time as my wife (who ordered a salad). My food came out before almost everyone else's. My host didn't get his food until almost an hour after I got mine. My wife's salad came out waay after my fries and sandwich, both of which required more preparation than her salad. I ended up not actually eating my sandwich out of politeness to those who hadn't gotten their food yet. And the appetizers? Those came out AFTER everyone's actual dinner. I also ordered a fountain root beer soda, and I'm fairly certain they had to go find the roots at a local farm and squeeze them into a cup in order to get it to me because it took an exorbitantly long amount of time to get it. You have to make a special request for straws here. I'm also pretty sure they had to import the plastic, cut and roll it and then wrap it in the paper before it could get to me. Took so long to get a straw I almost made the waitress take the drink off the bill.  When you combine this experience with how difficult the place is to get into and out of due to limited parking and heavy traffic in the area, it makes the trip (a 40 minute drive from my house) not well worth it.  My wife also noted that because of the $5 cover charge, the business made more than $45 from our table just for simple privilege of playing a few rounds of Apples to Apples.

The chai tea latte was very good and the portabella sandwich was very good. However, they need more kitchen staff. We waited for 45+ minutes for two sandwiches. The fries were cold. The chicken pesto was soggy and stale, which is a weird combo to eat. The croutons in the salad were stale. The service was very good! The atmosphere was VERY loud.  I feel like, if they don't get more kitchen staff and continue with the long waits for food then the board games should be free to play.  Honestly, if not for the wait I would have given a 4 star.

This place is amazing! $5 to play unlimited games cannot be beat, and the food is great! I also really appreciate the “game gurus” that are available to teach you the nuances of any game that you could ever play! The inclusion of them in this really relaxing space is very thoughtful. Overall, this is a great place to spend a day chilling with friends! :)
Great service.
It's the perfect spot to chill for a drink or breakfast a hidden gem

The best coffee (selection and quality) for miles, tons of board game selection, very warm and comfortable atmosphere. $5 a person for gaming can seem high, but it easy to burn many hours here to get your money's worth. Food is also good, perhaps overpriced.
Great game selection!
Great Korean bbq sandwich
Loved this place. We were here Saturday night. And the atmosphere and vibe was just perfect.

Board and brew is a lot of fun! They have plenty of board games for unlimited fun. Recommended to come early as it fills up quickly with other gamers. Happy hour is from 3-6, they have a lot of great beers for a cheaper price. They have a good selection of food with a equal vegetarian and normal options.

Not a terrible place to play a board game, but the food and drink are a touch expensive for what you get. Overall, not terrible, but maybe play here and eat/drink elsewhere.  EDIT: To expand on specifics, our table ordered two plates of pickle chips, some pretzel bites, mac and cheese and a cold soup.  The pickle chips were unusual in that they were corn breaded, but were quite good. The Cold Soup was interesting, a good adventure that was extremely not standard faire. The pretzel bites were not bad, but not necessarily cuisine. Sorta what you might expect. The Mac and cheese was mediocre, and while we did have fun playing pandemic, we were suggested a 2nd game by our game guru who gave us a game where 2 out of 4 of us were dead in the game by turn 3. Additionally, we rarely saw our waitress, not to try to pile it on.  Do I think it was all Board and Brews fault? Of course not, but an overall not fantastic experience was made worse by the pricing, that's all. A good place to try a beer and do a board game, but maybe skip dinner is my advice. That, or maybe avoid the appetizers menu? Unsure of the solution here, I just know our experience could've been better.
A huge variety of board games to play and comfortable seating. Milkshakes are lacking a little flavor but still made a good experience.

They have an excellent selection of games and good food.  Their gaming tables and seats are not ideal unless you are playing party games.  And they have all hard surfaces (no sound damping ceiling or wall tiles) so the place is a loud roar.  But we had fun.
Helpful, pleasant staff; large selection of board games; delicious food; and a variety of seating to either lounge or get serious about gaming... Definitely coming back for more fun!

Three stars is a compromise here.  There are reasons that it should be higher and reasons that it should be lower.  I'm not sure if it's because UMCP is out for the summer or what, but the hours posted on the website and on the Google maps entry are wrong.  My wife and a friend came in to eat, drink, and play a game.  It was only a little after 10:00 when we went in and the website said that Board and Brew was open until 1:00 AM so we thought we had plenty of time.  We ordered a round of drinks and some foods (sliders, old bay fries, and pickle chips) that came out in a reasonable amount of time and were all tasty and appropriately priced!  The selection of games is quite large and the $5 charge per person to play seemed affordable.  We picked a game that we haven't played before but is closely related to one that we have at home and ordered another round.  We were going through the rules and the owner came over when he saw we were checking through the rulebook to give us some examples to clarify the ways that this game differed from the one we were used to.  We started playing the game and picked it up quickly and were having a good time.  Our waitress took a 20-30 minute or so break after 11:00 to eat, which we didn't have a problem with, but at 11:45 one of the wait staff came and asked if we wanted another round of drinks.  He informed us that they were closing in 15 minutes, which was a surprise but we took this to mean that this was last call for placing an order.  Five minutes later our waitress came up to ask if we needed anything else and to let us know that they were closing in 9 minutes but that "we could keep playing until then!"  It was frustrating after having her attention for half an hour or so less than an hour before close!  Really her going on break to eat had indicated that they were going to be open for a while longer!  So not only are the hours posted on the website and on Google maps wrong, but the closing time isn't just a cutoff for being served.  You have to literally stop playing and leave at closing time.  We had to quit about 10-15 minutes before finishing.  If we had understood this beforehand we probably wouldn't have paid the $15!  I'm new in the area, but I can't say that I've seen a bar that didn't just stop serving at closing time, but actually asked patrons to leave.  I would be more understanding if we were in the middle of Hogwarts Battle or Arkham Horror or something else that takes hours to play.  We appreciated the owner clarifying some rules, but he made no mention of the closing time to warn us that we might not finish!  All in all, this could have been a five star review if 1. the hours on the internet reflected reality - this should be an easy thing to adjust! 2. the rule that closing time = patrons have to leave was advertised anywhere. 3. we had any warning that we might not be able to finish the game that we effectively paid $15 to play. 4. we hadn't been without service for 25 minutes or so before being told twice within 5 minutes that we would have to leave in 15/10 minutes.
This is a really fun place with great wait staff and incredible board games.

I ordered the buffalo chicken sandwich, that tasted like dried twigs, and the brussel sprout it was way too greasy, and my spinach salad so dry of sauce, I believe the mill was downgraded to the point a penny-pinching, or otherwise to cook is not a cook, it tasted like Bodega food.
Incredibly helpful and friendly staff. If you're looking for a good place to study, hang out with friends, or grab a coffee I would definitely recommend it.

Friendly service, a creative menu and a huge selection of board games to play while you eat and hang out. As an added bonus they feature artwork from local artists all for sale.

This place is cozy and amazing, clean and the customer service was one of the best I ever seen. I live in Boston so I was just visiting. They had great food and unique drink choices on the menu. I ended up eating old bay fries and had a ginger beer and espresso drink combination. Yes of course you don't think these two things work together but they actually do. I tried to recreate it when I got home it was so good. If I could I would give this place 10 stars that how good the service and atmosphere was.
Great games, good food. Try the Old Bay fries!
A fun place to come and play games! For only $5 per person, you can play any of their games for as long as you want. Food and drinks aren't great, but maybe we just chose the wrong items.
Amazing food, great staff and awesome assortment of games. We truly enjoyed our evening there. Definitely will be frequenting this place seeing how I work just down the street.

Been here more times than I can count - a fantastic place to go with friends to play a couple board games ($5 unlimited gaming, hundreds and hundreds of games available plus experts there to help teach you games if need be), or a good study space if you like having a chatty background. Food is a little pricey, I really enjoy the small plates though - sweet potato fries, the quedadillas, the hummus plate, and the pretzel bites are all great!
Very reasonable and Nice place for having drinks and clubbing. I went there for a friend’s birthday and enjoyed a lot there. The crowd and ambiance was just mind blowing.
I could live here. Great coffee, beer, good food, and 700+ games... Awesome combination
Great selection of games. Wonderful tea latte. Friendly people. Less than stellar parking situation. The machines in the nearby lots are often broken.
There are so many fun board games and the food is really good. It’s well worth the money and I want to go back again

A lot of the novelty is the selection of board games to play (though you have to pay $5/person to play games—which seems steep to me). Food is decidedly just better than okay. The buffalo chicken sandwich I had was flavorful but soggy and mushy. My friend’s burger was overcooked and not well dressed. Service was very friendly but also very slow.
I wish there was something like this in Baltimore city! Great concept, great food and drinks!
Great concept, but terrible service. Food is average

I’ve been to this place couple of times and I love it. During the day, it’s a perfect place to grab a drink to get work done. At night, it becomes more of a social place because a lot of people come after work/school to play from their selection of more than 500 board games!!! 🤯 So perfect for groups!  The only reason I gave it a 4/5 stars is because I didn’t really like their food. They were a little salty. I haven’t tried everything on the menu but so far that’s my opinion.  Other than that, It’s a great place!
They got board games and coffee 10/10 hulk smash

Maybe they had an off day on our visit on April 21, 2019, but coffee was barely warm and not very tasty. Eggs were scorched, breakfast potatoes were not well seasoned, bacon was way too undercooked, however, the sourdough toast was good. Wouldn’t return based on this experience.
Great espresso with every board game you can think of

I love Board & Brew. They have pretty yummy cinnamon pretzel bites, and the vibe is chill, hipster-ish, but really awesome. They have a wicked cool [board] game collection, and it is definitely worth popping in with a few friends to play a few rounds. Their food is apparently pretty good as well. I haven't been here in a minute because at one point, their menu wasn't vegan-friendly. I haven't checked back to determine whether it is or is not, but I highly recommend checking them out, if not for the food, then for their games collection.

My personal favorite place to spend some quality time with friends after a long day at UMD. The game selection is unparalleled in my experience, they have every game I have ever enjoyed and have introduced me to some new ones as well. On top of that, their food selection and quality is underrated. I have definitely come more than once solely for a good meal. Their alcohol selection is fine, they do have good happy hour deals as well. I also recommend trivia night as a fun evening for anyone looking to blow a little steam during the week.
Great place to eat, play board games, and have fun with friends.  Game guru was very helpful.
Great for people into board games

Loved this place. We were here Saturday night. And the atmosphere and vibe was just perfect. It’s a wonderful place where you can spend hours and not be bored. The game master has a personality and there are plenty of games to keep you busy. Fun place to hang out with friends if you want something different from drinking and getting wasted.
Really wouldn't reccomend going here. Service/food quality is way too inconsistent and they act like they don't see a problem with how things are run.
Amazing and fun! Great coffee and [insert favorite curse word here]-ton of games.

One of my new favorite spots to go. Love the staff. Great selection of board games. Coffee, beer, tea, homemade soda, and food. What more could you ask for in a place.
We love to go here and try out a game to see if it’s worth buying for our own collection. A beverage for every palate... the homemade sodas are great. This is now our default date spot.

Love the comfy couches, I fall asleep all the time! Happy hour specials and the light fare are great!!!

I come here on an almost weekly basis for D&D. Staff is both knowledgeable about their games and incredibly nice and accommodating. The game selection is impressive and the food is good, except for the buffalo chicken sandwich which is PHENOMENAL. I also love the seasonal drinks - bring back the sangria! 10/10

Great little spot to hangout, study, play board games, or just grab a small meal and drink to go. The entire menu is mostly oriented towards a small meal or light snack so don't expect to fill up on just 1 portion. Lots of tables for eating/snacking, studying with power outlets, and couches for playing board games.They even offer unlimited board games for a small fee which allows you to indulge in their massive selection with hundreds of individual sets to play with your friends. While the ambiance is perfect, food was tasty as long as the expectation that it's not a massive meal is in place, service could be better. We ordered some food which was not sent to the kitchen so it was over an hour before we received what we ordered. Water cups sat empty for long stretches at a time. Thankfully the owner is extremely competent and apologetic and comped our food costs due to the delay which wasn't necessary but extremely impressed. Come support a local business near the UMD campus.

Mistook my order multiple times, but I am a special case since I have Crohn's disease. The waiter gave me the meal for free after the 3rd time getting it incorrectly. They have great customer service, delicious food, and a bunch of games.

Genius idea! This is such a great date night or family night. Delicious food. Lemonade was a little watered down. Servers were very pleasing and patience. Bathrooms are clean. Love that you can purchase authentic art work. Pleasant ambiance, too.

Attentive and knowledgeable staff. Great place to go if you needed advice for gifting a board game. WiFi is good. Ben's Abomination breakfast sandwich is how you should be making breakfast sandwiches.
Great food and customer service!
Great Service
Fun place. Good customer service. Friendly staff. Enormous collection of board games
Super helpful staff, prompt service, so many games to choose from. Looking forward to coming in again for some Magic The Gathering on Wednesdays!

Our hostess was Sharon (not sure if I remember the name correctly). She was really sweet. And the other staff was really nice too. Great place to hang out with friends, choose from a wide variety of board games to play! Good food and coffee are a plus.

Board and brew has a very fun and vibrant atmosphere. $5 unlimited games is great too. It falls a little short with food/service. Super cool place, love the atmosphere and the staff was great and helped us pick a game to learn to play.
Really fun experience. All the food tastes great. Coffee was awesome. The board games were a lot of fun and the game guru was very helpful in explaining any games we didn’t know how to play.

Food was amazing and it was literally like the place of wit and competition with booz added.  So great

This is THE local hang out Cafe! With great foods, great ambiance, and great customer service this is definitely a local favorite. The area has a lot of parking really close in a paid parking lot.

I really like the idea of a place like this. Let's start of with the good, the atmosphere is really interesting. It really gives off that college, sort of 'hipster' vibe. The selection of games is AMAZING, though some games really look like they've been through it all. I wonder I'd they have a classic deck of cards. The music choice is different from what you hear of the radio these days, but it feels like a nice blast to the early 2000's, when alternative rock was the thing.  So it's $5 just to play the games, which is alright if you have time to spend hours playing games and get the most out of your money. I do not suggest this place if you just want to play a quick round. The food prices are pretty outrageous if you ask me. My suggestion: eat before you  come here. I had a problem with my order. My friend order the 3 sliders, which came with ketchup and we're in normal slider buns. I ordered the same thing a couple minutes later, but mine was a normal hamburger sliced into 3 pieces. Mine had tomatoes, but no ketchup. It tasted extremely dry and after two, I had to call and ask for ketchup, which surprisingly was still in stock. I wonder what happened with my order. The service was really nice though.

Decent coffee, but that's it, and it's overpriced. No good vegetarian/vegan options, and poor customer service. If you're into board games, maybe there's something here for you. But for coffee, food, or drinks, you're better off going to NuVegan, Vigilante, or sweetgreen, instead.
